    <item>
      <title>欧盟将对中国电动汽车关税进行投票</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-04/eu-set-to-vote-on-tariffs-targeting-electric-vehicles-from-china</link>
      <description><![CDATA[欧盟成员国将于周五投票决定是否对中国产电动汽车征收高达 45% 的关税，这一决定可能会进一步加剧欧盟与北京方面的紧张关系。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-04/eu-set-to-vote-on-tariffs-targeting-electric-vehicles-from-china</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Oct 2024 03:41:19 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>欧洲资金短缺的政府转向企业利润</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-04/italy-france-plan-higher-taxes-on-companies-to-fix-budgets</link>
      <description><![CDATA[法国和意大利希望向企业征收更多税收，以控制膨胀的预算赤字并确保其在债券投资者中的信誉。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-04/italy-france-plan-higher-taxes-on-companies-to-fix-budgets</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Oct 2024 03:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>日本央行行长石破茂寻求与日本央行行长上田保持一致</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-04/japan-s-ishiba-seeks-to-show-alignment-with-boj-governor-ueda</link>
      <description><![CDATA[日本首相石破茂试图表明，他并未就利率政策向日本央行施压，并表示他赞同日本央行行长上田和夫的观点，即在对利率做出任何调整之前，还有时间评估市场和经济状况。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-04/japan-s-ishiba-seeks-to-show-alignment-with-boj-governor-ueda</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 04 Oct 2024 00:52:20 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
